quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,88,"And he cast a look at the stars."
  37,89,"And said, "
  37,90,"So they turned away from him, departing."
  38,67,"Say, "
  38,68,"From which you turn away."
  38,69,"I had no knowledge of the exalted assembly [of angels] when they were disputing [the creation of Adam]."
  39,52,"Do they not know that Allāh extends provision for whom He wills and restricts [it]? Indeed in that are signs for a people who believe."
  39,53,"Say, ",footnotes:1:[For those who repent and correct themselves.]
  39,54,"And return [in repentance] to your Lord and submit to Him before the punishment comes upon you; then you will not be helped."
  40,31,"Like the custom of the people of Noah and of ʿAad and Thamūd and those after them. And Allāh wants no injustice for [His] servants."
  40,32,"And O my people, indeed I fear for you the Day of Calling{1} -",footnotes:1:[i.e., the Day of Judgement, when the criminals will cry out in terror, the people will call to each other (see 7:44-51), and the angels will call out the results of each person's judgement.]
  40,33,"The Day you will turn your backs fleeing; there is not for you from Allāh any protector. And whoever Allāh sends astray - there is not for him any guide."
  41,10,"And He placed on it [i.e., the earth] firmly set mountains over its surface, and He blessed it and determined therein its [creatures'] sustenance in four days without distinction{1} - for [the information of] those who ask.",footnotes:1:[Also "four equal days" or "four days of completion."]
  41,11,"Then He directed Himself{1} to the heaven while it was smoke and said to it and to the earth, ",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:19.],footnotes:2:[Literally, "become" or "do [as commanded]."]
  41,12,"And He completed them as seven heavens within two days and inspired [i.e., made known] in each heaven its command. And We adorned the nearest heaven with lamps [i.e., stars, for beauty] and as protection.{1} That is the determination of the Exalted in Might, the Knowing.",footnotes:1:[From the devils who attempt to steal information from the angels.]
